# Do Not Run npm/pnpm Scripts

NEVER execute npm, pnpm, yarn, or bun scripts (e.g. `pnpm process:feed`, `npm run dev`, `pnpm test:agent`).

The user runs these themselves. Running them can trigger expensive side effects (API calls, Firestore writes, long-running pipelines).

## Allowed

- Linting and type-checking tools directly (e.g. `tsc --noEmit`, read_lints)
- Build commands only when explicitly requested by the user

## When a script is needed

Show the exact command for the user to run. Do not execute it.

Example:

```bash
pnpm --filter @bwfish/server dev
```
